From b45f916acccc39d2cabd61e0ab49b38873fa23fa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramasamy Kaliappan <quic_rkaliapp@quicinc.com>
Date: Fri, 28 Feb 2025 16:49:59 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Fix hostapd Crashes Due to
 Interface Setup Failures

Hostapd crashes when it fails to set up the interface in
hostapd_add_iface due to invalid channel information, followed by
toggling the WiFi down and up.

Currently, when the interface setup fails, it only deinitializes
the driver. The BSS link is not deinitialized, which causes the
hostapd crash.

Add the fix to deinitialize the BSS link if the interface setup
fails.

Signed-off-by: Ramasamy Kaliappan <quic_rkaliapp@quicinc.com>
---
 src/ap/hostapd.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/src/ap/hostapd.c
+++ b/src/ap/hostapd.c
@@ -4414,6 +4414,8 @@ int hostapd_add_iface(struct hapd_interf
 				goto fail;
 
 			if (hostapd_setup_interface(hapd_iface)) {
+				/* Deinit link for the first bss */
+				hostapd_bss_link_deinit(hapd_iface->bss[0]);
 				hostapd_deinit_driver(
 					hapd_iface->bss[0]->driver,
 					hapd_iface->bss[0]->drv_priv,
